File: The Democratic Alliance leader, John Steenhuisen. JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) has announced John Steenhuisen as its new leader. Steenhuisen was elected at the party's two-day virtual congress. The party's leadership race was a hotly contested one between Steenhuisen and Mbali Ntuli. READ: DA to announce new leader Steenhuisen has been the party's interim leader after Mmusi Maimane’s exit from the DA.